National Security Advisor Rice and Presidential Foreign Policy Advisor Ushakov had a positive meeting at the G20 Summit in St. Petersburg. They discussed the state of U.S.-Russian relations and areas of future cooperation. They also talked about Syria, with Rice emphasizing the need for the Assad regime to be held accountable for their use of chemical weapons. Rice also expressed support for the upcoming Sochi Olympics and the importance of ensuring a secure event. Despite challenges in the bilateral relationship, Rice welcomed ongoing communication and cooperation on mutual interests.